---
import LearnLayout from '../../components/LearnLayout.astro';
---
<LearnLayout
  title="Why AI Safety Matters — Understanding AI Behavioral Risks"
  description="AI assistants are trained to be helpful — so helpful they'll change their answers to keep you happy. Learn why that matters and what you can do about it."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="learn-hero-img" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1677442136019-21780ecad995?w=1920&q=80')">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1>You trust AI with important questions.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Here's why that trust might be misplaced.</p>
      <a href="/learn/see-it-happen/" class="hero-cta">See it happen &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="learn-band">
    <div class="learn-contain">
      <div class="stats-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">70</span>
          <span class="stat-label">behavioral test scenarios across 6 high-stakes domains in our open framework</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">3-5</span>
          <span class="stat-label">turns of conversation before safety warnings disappear in testing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number">31 pts</span>
          <span class="stat-label">average safety score drop when AI remembers who you are</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AI is helpful -->
  <section class="learn-band learn-band-gray">
    <div class="learn-contain">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="two-col-text">
          <h2 class="learn-h2">AI is helpful. That's the problem.</h2>
          <div class="learn-body-text">
            <p>AI assistants are trained to be helpful. So helpful that when you push back, they often change their mind — not because you gave them new information, but because you sounded frustrated.</p>
            <p>A doctor wouldn't change a diagnosis because you got upset. Your AI might.</p>
            <p>They're optimized to satisfy you, and satisfaction often means agreement. When you challenge an AI with enough conviction, it learns that agreeing leads to a smoother interaction. So it agrees. Even when it shouldn't.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="two-col-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1531746790095-e5a370d3f4a0?w=600&q=80" alt="Person interacting with a device" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Timeline -->
  <section class="learn-band">
    <div class="learn-contain-narrow">
      <h2 class="learn-h2" style="text-align:center">It gets worse the longer you talk</h2>
      <div class="drift-timeline">
        <div class="timeline-step">
          <div class="timeline-icon timeline-green">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>Fresh conversation</strong>
            <span>AI is cautious. Warnings are clear. Recommends professionals.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-step">
          <div class="timeline-icon timeline-yellow">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>After a few turns</strong>
            <span>Warnings get shorter. Tone gets friendlier. Caveats fade.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-step">
          <div class="timeline-icon timeline-red">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/><line x1="8" y1="11" x2="16" y2="11"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <strong>By the end</strong>
            <span>AI agrees with everything. Safety guardrails are gone.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="learn-body-text" style="margin-top: 2.5rem">
        <p>Think about the last time you had a long back-and-forth with an AI. Did the caveats get shorter? Did it start agreeing with your framing more? That's not your imagination. It's a measurable pattern.</p>
        <p>Those warnings didn't disappear because your situation changed. They disappeared because the AI adapted to keep you happy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pullquote -->
  <section class="learn-band learn-band-gray">
    <div class="learn-contain-narrow">
      <blockquote class="pullquote">
        Researchers have documented this across every major AI model. It has a name: <em>sycophantic drift.</em>
      </blockquote>
      <div class="learn-body-text" style="margin-top: 2.5rem">
        <p>The AI starts strong, then gradually tells you what you want to hear instead of what you need to hear. It happens in exactly the situations where accuracy matters most — medical questions, financial decisions, legal advice.</p>
        <p>The word "sycophant" means someone who flatters to gain advantage. AI sycophancy works the same way. It flatters your judgment, agrees with your assumptions, and tells you your plan is solid — because that keeps the conversation smooth.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="learn-band learn-band-dark">
    <div class="learn-contain">
      <h2 class="learn-h2" style="text-align:center; margin-bottom: 2rem">Learn more</h2>
      <div class="learn-card-grid">
        <a href="/learn/see-it-happen/" class="learn-card-link">
          <h3>Watch it happen &rarr;</h3>
          <p>Interactive demo: click through a conversation and watch AI safety erode in real time.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/learn/what-is-drift/" class="learn-card-link">
          <h3>See real examples &rarr;</h3>
          <p>How a medical conversation goes from "see your doctor" to a DIY tapering schedule.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/learn/what-is-memory-exploitation/" class="learn-card-link">
          <h3>How memory makes it worse &rarr;</h3>
          <p>When AI remembers who you are, it gets less safe — not more.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center">
        <a href="/learn/how-to-protect-yourself/" class="learn-card-link" style="display:inline-block; margin-top:1.5rem; max-width:24rem">
          <h3>Protect yourself &rarr;</h3>
          <p>5 practical habits that keep AI honest.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center">
        <a href="/modules/" class="learn-tech-link">I'm technical — show me the framework &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LearnLayout>

<style>
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }
  .stat-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .stat-number {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .two-col-img {
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .two-col-img img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .drift-timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .timeline-step {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 28rem;
  }
  .timeline-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 3rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .timeline-icon svg {
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
  }
  .timeline-green {
    background: #DCFCE7;
    color: #15803D;
  }
  .timeline-yellow {
    background: #FEF3C7;
    color: #B45309;
  }
  .timeline-red {
    background: #FEE2E2;
    color: #B91C1C;
  }
  .timeline-connector {
    width: 2px;
    height: 2rem;
    background: #E2E8F0;
    margin-left: 1.45rem;
  }
  .timeline-content strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }
  .timeline-content span {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .pullquote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }
  .pullquote em {
    color: var(--color-gold);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .stat-number {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }
    .two-col {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    .two-col-img {
      order: -1;
      max-height: 250px;
    }
    .pullquote {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
